[[File:Domsjo Fabriker.jpg|right|thumb|Domsjö Fabriker]]
'''Domsjö Fabriker''' is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[Refining|refinery]] located in [[Örnsköldsvik]] that converts raw forest materials into specialty [[cellulose]], [[lignin]], and [[bio-ethanol]]. In 2000 it was spun off from the forest company [[Mo och Domsjö AB]] (MoDo), of which it had been a part since the early 20th century, and sold to a private consortium. On April 18, 2011, it was announced that [[India]]'s [[Aditya Birla Group]] had acquired the company for US$340 million.

