'''Heneicosylic acid''', or ''heneicosanoic acid'', is a 21-[[carbon]] long-chain [[saturated fatty acid]] with the [[chemical formula]] CH<sub>3</sub>(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>19</sub>COOH. It has shown relevance in the production of foams, paints, and related viscous materials.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Alternate Measurement of the Viscosity Peak in Heneicosanoic Acid Monolayers|journal=Langmuir|volume=16|issue=26|pages=10553–10555|doi=10.1021/la0006925|year=2000|last1=Ghaskadvi|first1=R. S|last2=Dennin|first2=Michael}}</ref>
